Starring multiple Emmy nominee Michael C. Hall as America‚Äôs favorite serial killer Dexter Morgan, the special event series DEXTER: NEW BLOOD will premiere Sunday, November 7 at 9 p.m. ET/PT on SHOWTIME. Set 10 years after Dexter went missing in the eye of Hurricane Laura, the series finds him living under an assumed name in the small town of Iron Lake, New York. Dexter may be embracing his new life, but in the wake of unexpected events in this close-knit community, his Dark Passenger beckons. Joining Hall, the cast also includes Julia Jones (The Mandalorian), Alano Miller (Sylvie‚Äôs Love), Johnny Sequoyah (Believe), Jack Alcott (THE GOOD LORD BIRD) and Clancy Brown (The Crown, BILLIONS). Reuniting Hall with original series showrunner Clyde Phillips, DEXTER: NEW BLOOD is currently in production on 10 one-hour episodes in Western Massachusetts.

Oscar nominee Denis Villeneuve (‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù ‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049‚Äù) directs Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures‚Äô ‚ÄúDune,‚Äù the big-screen adaptation of Frank Herbert‚Äôs seminal bestseller of the same name.
A mythic and emotionally charged hero‚Äôs journey, ‚ÄúDune‚Äù tells the story of Paul Atreides, a brilliant and gifted young man born into a great destiny beyond his understanding, who must travel to the most dangerous planet in the universe to ensure the future of his family and his people. As malevolent forces explode into conflict over the planet‚Äôs exclusive supply of the most precious resource in existence‚Äîa commodity capable of unlocking humanity‚Äôs greatest potential‚Äîonly those who can conquer their fear will survive.
The film stars Oscar nominee Timoth√©e Chalamet (‚ÄúCall Me by Your Name,‚Äù ‚ÄúLittle Women‚Äù), Rebecca Ferguson (‚ÄúStephen King‚Äôs Doctor Sleep,‚Äù ‚ÄúMission: Impossible ‚Äì Fallout‚Äù), Oscar Isaac (the ‚ÄúStar Wars‚Äù franchise) Oscar nominee Josh Brolin (‚ÄúMilk,‚Äù ‚ÄúAvengers: Infinity War‚Äù), Stellan Skarsg√•rd (HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúChernobyl,‚Äù ‚ÄúAvengers: Age of Ultron‚Äù), Dave Bautista (the ‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy‚Äù films, ‚ÄúAvengers: Endgame‚Äù), Stephen McKinley Henderson (‚ÄúFences,‚Äù ‚ÄúLady Bird‚Äù), Zendaya (‚ÄúSpider-Man: Homecoming,‚Äù HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúEuphoria‚Äù), Chang Chen (‚ÄúMr. Long,‚Äù ‚ÄúCrouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon‚Äù), David Dastmalchian (‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Dark Knight‚Äù), Sharon Duncan-Brewster (‚ÄúRogue One: A Star Wars Story,‚Äù Netflix‚Äôs ‚ÄúSex Education‚Äù), with Oscar nominee Charlotte Rampling (‚Äú45 Years,‚Äù ‚ÄúAssassin‚Äôs Creed‚Äù), with Jason Momoa (‚ÄúAquaman,‚Äù HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúGame of Thrones‚Äù), and Oscar winner Javier Bardem (‚ÄúNo Country for Old Men,‚Äù ‚ÄúSkyfall‚Äù).
Villeneuve directed ‚ÄúDune‚Äù from a screenplay by Jon Spaihts and Villeneuve and Eric Roth based on the novel of the same name written by Frank Herbert. Villeneuve also produced the film with Mary Parent, Cale Boyter and Joe Caracciolo, Jr. The executive producers are Tanya Lapointe, Joshua Grode, Herbert W. Gains, Jon Spaihts, Thomas Tull, Brian Herbert, Byron Merritt and Kim Herbert.
Behind the scenes, Villeneuve reteamed with two-time Oscar-nominated production designer Patrice Vermette (‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù ‚ÄúSicario,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Young Victoria‚Äù), two-time Oscar-nominated editor Joe Walker (‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049,‚Äù ‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù ‚Äú12 Years a Slave‚Äù), two-time Oscar-winning visual effects supervisor Paul Lambert (‚ÄúFirst Man,‚Äù ‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049‚Äù), and Oscar-winning special effects supervisor Gerd Nefzer (‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049‚Äù). He also collaborated for the first time with Oscar-nominated director of photography Greig Fraser (‚ÄúLion,‚Äù ‚ÄúZero Dark Thirty,‚Äù ‚ÄúRogue One: A Star Wars Story‚Äù); three-time Oscar-nominated costume designer Jacqueline West (‚ÄúThe Revenant,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Curious Case of Benjamin Button,‚Äù ‚ÄúQuills‚Äù) and costume designer Robert Morgan; and stunt coordinator Tom Struthers (‚ÄúThe Dark Knight‚Äù trilogy, ‚ÄúInception‚Äù). Oscar-winning and multiple Oscar-nominated composer Hans Zimmer (‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049,‚Äù ‚ÄúInception,‚Äù ‚ÄúGladiator,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Lion King‚Äù) is creating the score.

Pictures and Legendary Pictures Present a Legendary Pictures Production, a Film by Denis Villeneuve, ‚ÄúDune.‚Äù The film is slated to be released in select theaters in 2D and 3D and IMAX and on HBO Max on October 22, 2021 and will be available on HBO Max‚Äôs Ad-Free plan in 4K UHD, HDR10, Dolby Vision and Dolby Atmos (English Only) on supported devices for 31 days from theatrical release.

Record-breaking floods have killed at least 150 people in western Europe. Most of the deaths are in Germany's west - where the disaster area stretches between the towns of Heinsberg, Erftstadt and Ahrweiler, near the border with the Netherlands and Belgium. More than 130 people have been confirmed dead and more than a thousand are still missing. President Frank-Walter Steinmeier has promised support for victims' families, and to the damaged towns. In Belgium, at least 20 people have died in the flooding. The government has declared Tuesday a national day of mourning. The towns of Li√®ge in Belgium and Venlo in the Netherlands have been hit hard. In Venlo 10,000 people were told to evacuate, as well as 200 patients from a hospital. In Liege, the swollen Meuse river has burst.
